  <h1>
   view_get_surface_id
  </h1>
  This function can be used to retrieve the unique ID value for the surface assigned to the given view port (will return -1 if no surface has been assigned).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">view_get_surface_id(view_port)
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      view_port
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The view port to target (0 - 7)
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Surfaces/surface_create.htm">
 Surface ID
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if view_get_surface_id(0) == -1
{
    view_set_surface_id(0, global.vSurf);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check to see if a surface has been assigned to the view port[0] and if it has not then one is assigned.
 </body>
